 drones are possible due to closed-loop control systems. An autonomous flight is possible due to automated individual parts of drones. The key purpose of an autonomous drone is to lessen human input and error through the help of Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) [8]. Carev, et al. [9], invented a universal metric to measure research programs, planning innovative programs, and comparing efforts to develop autonomous control technology. This metric is known as the Autonomous Control Level (ACL) for a UAV. The ACL metric system was made by Air Force Research Laboratory’s Air Vehicles Directorate. Most UAVs today which",
